  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 4.1,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "[BEEPING]",
      "word_count": 1
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 1,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "Strange.",
      "word_count": 1
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 1,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "Strange.",
      "word_count": 1
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 1,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "But as a child, you accept things.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 1,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "One occasion, though, stands out in my mind.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 1,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "On that occasion, [PAUSES FOR 3 SECONDS] the Germans came in, and they decided to remove a dining room suite which had belonged to my uncle.",
      "word_count": 26
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 1,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "His flat had been bombed, and some of his things were brought to my grandparents' flat.",
      "word_count": 16
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 2,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "On this occasion, they started-- the soldiers started carrying the furniture away, when I suddenly realized that in the sideboard drawer, I had left my stamp collection.",
      "word_count": 27
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 2,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "Now, that upset me very much, because it was something which belonged to me, and I wanted to have it.",
      "word_count": 20
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 2,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "So I rushed to my grandmother and said, they've got my stamps, can you get them?",
      "word_count": 16
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 2,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "And she spoke very good German.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 2,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "She had been educated.",
      "word_count": 4
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 2,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "She went to boarding school in Germany in her younger days.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 2,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "And she went out onto the stairs and said to the soldier, my little granddaughter had left her stamps-- could she have them?",
      "word_count": 23
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 3,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "And he turned around and hit her across her face.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 3,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "And that is something which really frightened me and shocked me.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 3,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "Proof, that I remember it more than 60 years on.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 3,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "[PAUSES FOR 5 SECONDS] The other thing was that there were big notices on the entrance to the apartment, saying that this was a Jewish apartment, and that nothing should be taken away without permission, because all the contents belonged to the German Reich, or whatever it-- but we were not supposed to take anything other than personal belongings out of the apartment.",
      "word_count": 63
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 3,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "And other Germans could come and take things away, but nothing belonged to us anymore.",
      "word_count": 15
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 3,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "But other than that, of course, I couldn't go to school.",
      "word_count": 11
    }
  ],
